seal     : Life as a process, not a substance — and a process can run on anything. In a computer, simple rules conjure things that flock, hunt, heal their wounds, reproduce, and evolve, with no chemistry at all. Artificial life asks whether 'alive' is about what a thing is made of, or only about what it does.
